Method Detail

registerMenu

public static void registerMenu(java.lang.Class<? extends ContextAwareMenu> menuClass,
                                java.lang.String commandKey)
Registers a new menu within MCT. Each menu within MCT has an identifier, its command key. This command key is used to look up the menu by ID using getMenu(String, ActionContextImpl).

Parameters:
menuClass - the class that implements the menu
commandKey - the unique identifier for the new menu

getMenu

public static ContextAwareMenu getMenu(java.lang.String commandKey,
                                       ActionContextImpl context)
Finds a menu that has the given command key and is applicable in the given action context. If more than one such menu exits, return the first one registered.

Parameters:
commandKey - the command key of menus to find
context - the action context in which the menu should be applicable
Returns:
the applicable menu

registerAction

public static void registerAction(java.lang.Class<? extends ContextAwareAction> actionClass,
                                  java.lang.String commandKey)
Registers an action for use within MCT. An action is associated with a command key, which ties a menu entry to an action.

Parameters:
actionClass - the class implementing the action
commandKey - the command key for the action

unregisterAction

public static void unregisterAction(java.lang.Class<? extends ContextAwareAction> actionClass,

Removes an action with the given class and command key.

Parameters:
actionClass - the class implementing the action
commandKey - the command key for the action to remove
